                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d60">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.42790H/54a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Afghanistan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-29T22:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 29, 1943—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>54. Your 85, April 20. We agree that this appears to be an excellent opportunity
                    for this Government to be of assistance to Afghanistan. We are accordingly
                    actively working on the matter and are in a position already to present the
                    names of some suitable candidates for the positions of teachers and engineers.
                    Is it the desire of the Afghan Government that the contractual arrangements
                    should be effected through the new Minister when he arrives or does it wish to
                    suggest some other procedure? We doubt if the salaries offered will be adequate
                    for the high type of persons whom we would want for these positions, but for
                    your strictly confidential information consideration is being given to the
                    possibility of supplementing the salaries offered from funds which may be made
                    available from other sources.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
